    {
      "id": "sybil_9_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This specimen retains its original 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary powerplant, delivering linear boost through the factory-spec Hitachi HT12 turbines. The chassis remains exceptionally rigid, benefiting from the lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension and a perfectly balanced 50/50 weight distribution. Recent compression tests confirm apex seal integrity across all rotors, meeting high-performance factory tolerances. The five-speed manual transmission features crisp synchronizer engagement, paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. Finished in Montego Blue with a flawless tan leather interior, this FD represents a rare opportunity for the discerning collector seeking a mechanically unmolested, investment-grade rotary icon.",
